# {{APP_NAME}}

A bare React Native app (no Expo) with streaming on-device chat, powered by
[`llama.rn`](https://github.com/mybigday/llama.rn) and
[`@machine/activation-sdk`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@machine/activation-sdk)
+ [`@machine/ui`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@machine/ui).

## Prerequisites

Follow the React Native CLI setup guide for your platform:
<https://reactnative.dev/docs/environment-setup>

You'll need Xcode (for iOS) and/or Android Studio + the Android SDK (for
Android), plus Node 20+.

## Get started

```bash
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} install
npx pod-install           # iOS only — installs CocoaPods deps
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} run ios      # or: {{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} run android
```

In another terminal, start the Metro dev server (if it didn't auto-start):

```bash
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} run start
```

`llama.rn` needs the New Architecture enabled. Generate native projects
(`npx react-native-community/cli init`) with `--new-architecture`, or flip
`newArchEnabled=true` in `android/gradle.properties` and
`RCT_NEW_ARCH_ENABLED=1` in the iOS Podfile.

## What's in `src/`

- **`llamaRuntime.ts`** — an `ActivationRuntime` adapter that wraps
  `llama.rn`'s `initLlama` + session streaming. Swap or extend it freely.
- **`App.tsx`** — wires `<MachineProvider>` around the chat screen, using
  a `Machine` constructed with the `llama.rn` runtime.
- **`ChatScreen.tsx`** — the chat UI. `useMachineModel({ cartridge })` picks
  the cartridge, `useInference(model)` drives streaming, and
  `<InferenceIndicator>` renders status.

## Pick a cartridge

`ChatScreen.tsx` loads `dev.machine.gemma-3n-e4b-it` by default. Browse
more on the cartridge catalog or publish your own with
`machine pack` + `machine publish`.

## Next steps

- Replace the placeholder cartridge id with your own cartridge.
- Style the UI to taste — everything in `@machine/ui/native` is unstyled
  and renders primitive `View` / `Text` so you can theme it freely.
- Add a `<ModelPicker>` screen for production flows where users pick the
  cartridge themselves.
- If you prefer Expo over bare RN, try `create-machine-app --template expo-local-chat`.
